sprint: S06
track: A
task: A2
title: "feat(brands): activate Marcrest in CROP-front manufacturer-config"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: high
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 (Ferris, Ventrac, McHale, Marcrest all needed in production)
  - CROP-front#1433 (McHale/Ventrac activation pattern — copy this)
  - CROP-front#1398 (Ferris activation pattern — copy this)
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]

impact: |
  Marcrest has no entry in MANUFACTURER_CONFIGS so `/parts/brand/marcrest` and
  `/parts-diagrams/marcrest` return 404. Activating it wires the brand into every
  route that reads MANUFACTURER_CONFIGS: brand hub page, parts-diagrams, equipment
  types API, sitemap generation, and the brands list page.

description: |
  Pattern: front#1433 (McHale). Steps:
  1. Add `marcrest` entry to MANUFACTURER_CONFIGS in `lib/db/manufacturer-config.ts`
     using `carriedIdentity("marcrest")`. Set `available: true, seoIndexed: false`.
     The `seoIndexed: false` keeps the page noindex,follow until John explicitly
     approves indexing — consistent with all other non-NH V2 brands.
  2. `AVAILABLE_MANUFACTURER_SLUGS` is derived automatically from the config —
     no manual additions needed.
  3. Verify `generateStaticParams()` on both brand pages now includes "marcrest"
     (the filter `c.available === true` drives it).
  4. Confirm `robotsForBrand("marcrest")` returns the correct noindex/follow preset
     (front#1397 pattern).
  5. Update `lib/seo-config.ts` or wherever brand-level OG defaults are set if
     Marcrest needs a custom accent color/branding config.

scope:
  in:
    - `lib/db/manufacturer-config.ts`: add marcrest entry
    - Check/add Marcrest to `lib/brand-branding.ts` (accent color) if that file
      has per-brand entries
    - Unit test for `getManufacturerConfig("marcrest")` → not null, available: true
  out:
    - Static content / imagery for the Marcrest landing page (Track B scope)
    - Marcrest data seeding in DB (Vova/Alex)
    - seoIndexed: true (not until John approves indexing)

invariants:
  - seoIndexed MUST be false — no brand reaches seoIndexed:true without explicit John approval
  - available: true is required for the route to activate
  - Canonical slug: "marcrest" (lowercase, no spaces)
  - vendorCode must match what hono uses in its vocabulary table ("MAR" or full name —
    verify against vocabulary-cache.ts DEFAULT_MANUFACTURERS or BRAND_REGISTRY)

acceptance:
  - `getManufacturerConfig("marcrest")` returns config with `available: true`
  - GET /parts/brand/marcrest → 200 (not 404) in dev build
  - GET /parts-diagrams/marcrest → 200 or graceful empty-state (no 500)
  - robots meta on /parts/brand/marcrest → noindex,follow (not noindex,nofollow)
  - Unit test passes

dep: A1 (hono BRAND_REGISTRY must have MAR before FE data fetch will populate)
output: lib/db/manufacturer-config.ts + optional lib/brand-branding.ts
